    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-soy-hake-with-black-bean-greens-and-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely slice your<strong> ginger</strong>, then chop into matchsticks as finely as you can</p><p>Combine your <strong>black bean paste</strong> with 25ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [40ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[50ml] </span><strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>black bean sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-soy-hake-with-black-bean-greens-and-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add your<strong> hake fillet[s]</strong> to a plate and drizzle your <strong>soy sauce</strong> all over</p><p>Turn the <strong>hake</strong> several times until the soy sauce fully soaks into the fish</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>cornflour </strong>all over and rub it into both sides of the fish until fully coated, then set aside for later</p><p>Tip: Coat the fish in the cornflour one side at a time to avoid stickiness!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-soy-hake-with-black-bean-greens-and-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut a piece[s] of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A3 paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>sliced ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in the middle with your <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>and <strong>black bean sauce</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the vegetables to form<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>sealed parcel[s]</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until tender \u2013 these are your <strong>black bean greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-soy-hake-with-black-bean-greens-and-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining sliced ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until crispy</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once crispy, transfer them to a bowl and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy ginger & garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-soy-hake-with-black-bean-greens-and-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to the heat with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated hake </strong>and cook for 8-10 min, turning once halfway until golden, crisp and cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy soy hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-soy-hake-with-black-bean-greens-and-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-soy-hake-with-black-bean-greens-and-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy soy hake</strong> with the<strong> cooked</strong> <strong>rice </strong>and <strong>black bean greens </strong>to the side and pour any <strong>remaining black bean sauce </strong>over the greens</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into small bowls and turn out</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>crispy ginger & garlic</strong> and <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> over the crispy soy hake and rice</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
